##Kubesystem Namespaces 

Check what namespaces are running in our nodes 

Command: kubectl get ns 
    Pay attention to 2 Namespaces (kube-node-lease and kube-public can be ignored)
        Default 
        kube-system 
Command - kubectl get pod 
    Won't see any pods unless deployed 
    The "default" namespace is used as a default when executing kubectl commands 
    Will need to specify other namespaces if necessary
    To specify command: kubectl get pod -n (specific NS - example: kube-system)
             